How to prepare catalog entries in oracle POOL dbs
  --download CondTools/OracleDBA from CMSSW CVS
  --cd CondTools/OracleDBA/src
  --change locally the "password" parameter in the authentication.xml file to correct ones 
  --./generate_oracle_catalog.sh oracleservicename
    example oracleservice names
    
    ./generate_oracle_catalog.sh orcon
    ./generate_oracle_catalog.sh cms_orcoff
    ./generate_oracle_catalog.sh cms_orcoff_val
    ./generate_oracle_catalog.sh cms_orcoff_int2r

How to prepare a detector pool schema 
  pool_build_object_relational_mapping -f mapping_CondIOV_2.0.xml -d CondCoreIOVService -c oracle://devdb10/CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -u CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -p ***
  pool_setup_database -f dbsetup_CondIOV_2.0.xml -d CondCoreIOVService -c oracle://devdb10/CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -u CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -p ***
  pool_build_object_relational_mapping -f mapping_EcalObjects_1.0.xml -d CondFormatsEcalObjects -c oracle://devdb10/CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -u CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -p ***
  pool_setup_database -f dbsetup_EcalObjects_1.0.xml -d CondFormatsEcalObjects -c oracle://devdb10/CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -u CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN -p ***
  sqlplus CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN@devdb10/*** < ../sql/createMetadata.sql
  sqlplus CMS_COND_ECAL_POOL_ADMIN@devdb10/*** < ../sql/addTime_2.0.sql
  Note: addTime_2.0.sql time type has to match the declared time type in mapping_CondIOV_2.0.xml

How to import pool schema to a production server